2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper formulates the spectrum leasing problem as a non-cooperative game, which falls under the domain of game theory. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves decision-making and optimization problems related to revenue maximization, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may involve security and privacy concerns related to spectrum leasing in a cognitive radio network. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may involve the study of social and information networks in the context of spectrum leasing and coordination between primary and secondary users.
